Title: Yang-Mills Instantons in the Gravitational Instanton Backgrounds
Authors: Hongsu Kim and Yongsung Yoon (Hanyang Univ., Korea)
Comments: 14pages, Revtex, version to appear in Phys. Lett. B
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B495 (2000) 169-175
\\
  The simplest and the most straightforward new algorithm for generating
solutions to (anti) self-dual Yang-Mills (YM) equation in the typical
gravitational instanton backgrounds is proposed. When applied to the Taub-NUT
and the Eguchi-Hanson metrics, the two best-known gravitational instantons, the
solutions turn out to be the rather exotic type of instanton configurations
carrying finite YM action but generally fractional topological charge values.
